+# Tidewatch5
+
+A tide prediction service that provides high and low tide information.
+
+## Shipshape
+
+This project uses [Shipshape](https://github.com/dmytri/shipshape), a context-isolated spec-driven workflow for coding agents.
+
+- **Stack**: JavaScript, Node.js, npm
+- **Specs**: `features/`
+- **Implementation**: `src/`
+- **Verification**: `features/support/`
+- **Assets**: `data/`
+
+## Installation
+
+```bash
+npm install
+```
+
+## Testing
+
+```bash
+npm test
+```
+
+## Usage
+
+The main function `nextHighTide` in `src/tide.js` takes a tide table and a timestamp, returning the next high tide after the given time.
+
+```javascript
+const { nextHighTide } = require('./src/tide');
+const tides = require('./data/tides.json');
+const nextTide = nextHighTide(tides, '2026-07-12T05:00:00Z');
+console.log(nextTide);
+```
